One more unwritten rule is:

Wtf is my exit plan. Do u have patience to hodl 6 months or 6 hours?

Wish you all happy investing and always DYOR.

Life is good üî•

8/9

Recap what does DYOR mean?

1. When is project launching? Are you buying pre or post reveal?
2. How active is community? Is the team still working & delivering announcements post reveal?
3. Who tf is the team? Their reputation?
4. Analysis of own budget. Am I overinvested?

7/9

My rule of thumb is never invest more than 10-15 percent of total liquidity on 1 single project.

When I bought 30 @KarafuruNFT it was huge conviction play and also less than 10% of my liquidity.

I believe they are a project that is doing so many things right.

6/9 üëÄ

Lastly once thing that does not get mentioned enough:

Take an analysis of your own budget before you invest.

If you have 10 eth and invest 10 eth in a project you are balls deep in it now. If floor drops you are probably not sleeping at night.

Why u did this?

5/9

The reason why this is so important because it will decide if:

A) will team rug or simply suck at what they do. 
B) will they continue building/have build reputable things before.

Teams are the heartbeat of communities and as we‚Äôve seen with @Pixelmon, experience matters.

4/9

Now that the project is going well something you should have already done is:

Who tf is the team? Who is the artist?

This can matter depending on project ambition. You need yo know team experience, ambitions, budget, reputation.

3/9

Second, how active is their discord post reveal ‚Äî Is team still working and being engaged?

- Engagement and further announcements post reveal tend to help floors recover.

The blend of marketing, community involvement and gram announcements are essential in this stage.

2/9

First, you should consider the following:

- When Is project launching? Is it revealed yet or not?

If you buy pre-reveal expect price correction post reveal.Usually prices dip post reveal. However strong projects tend to recover their floor very fast.

1/9

What does DYOR mean?

The worst mistake you can make in NFTs is buying ‚Äúthe next KONGZ‚Äù or ‚Äúthe next BAYC‚Äù etc.

You should not invest just based on ‚Äúoh it‚Äôs similar. It will probably surpass X or Y project‚Äù but invest on actual research.
